{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"immune-floury-toad","description":"## Why\n\nThe epic needs a project-owned Pass 1 finder that rejects concrete portability failures without demanding generic portability prose. The fresh-worktree experiment has already proven that the project overlay, prompt loader, and production fan-in mechanism support this extension shape.\n\n## What\n\nAdd and activate `project.portability` in the project criteria overlay, author its Pass 1 rubric prompt, and add focused integration tests for prompt resolution, scope routing, and production finding fan-in.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`\n- `.rebar/prompts/plan-review-project-portability.md`\n- `tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py`\n- Pass 1 discovery for both leaf and container tickets\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Pass 2 validity or impact logic\n- Pass 3 disposition logic\n- coaching moves\n- live semantic calibration\n- remediation of existing portability debt\n\n## Approach\n\nUse the existing project overlay seam rather than adding a built-in criterion. This keeps rebar-specific policy in the rebar repository while exercising the same supported extension boundary available to clients. Configure `exec: 1-TURN`, `facet: project-invariants`, `applies_at.scope: [container, leaf]`, `default_posture: blocking`, and `block_threshold: 0.9`, then add the id to `activate`.\n\nThe rubric must emit a finding only when it supplies all four parts needed by Pass 2: a plan citation, a materially different supported client shape, a causal failure mechanism, and a specific observable breakage scenario. Map those parts to `location`, `scenarios`, `finding`, and `evidence` respectively. Silence about portability is not a finding, and project-specific behavior placed behind project configuration or an explicit extension boundary remains allowed.\n\n## Test Strategy\n\nExercise the real overlay loader, prompt resolver, routing registry, and `ProductionBatchRunner` fan-in with deterministic fakes. Tests inspect the authored rubric contract; live LLM behavior belongs to the calibration child.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The overlay activates `project.portability` with the exact routing defaults in this plan. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k criterion_activation`.\n- [ ] The project rubric resolves through the production prompt loader for `project.portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k prompt_resolution`.\n- [ ] Both leaf and container plan reviews route the criterion and fan its findings into the production batch result. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k routing_and_fan_in`.\n- [ ] The rubric encodes the four-part finding contract and covers harness, target-project, platform-or-venue, and workspace-or-filesystem assumptions. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k rubric_contract`.\n- [ ] The rubric explicitly excludes missing portability prose and specialization behind project configuration or an explicit extension boundary. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_criterion.py -k false_positive_guards`.\n- [ ] Existing behavior remains unchanged when the project overlay is absent. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_criteria_overlay.py tests/unit/test_plan_review_production_runner.py`.\n","id":"3863-a783-b38f-4c8a","parent_id":"jira-reb-1003","priority":2,"tags":["plan-review","portability","project-criteria"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Activate the rebar portability finder"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784164041500193001,"uuid":"43c14435-4fea-4e96-b08f-4d7cd1ee1ffb"}